# Dual Version Updates

This project has two versions of the site that must stay in sync:

1. **Static HTML (GitHub Pages)**: Root-level `.html` files (`index.html`, `hax.html`, `research.html`, `foundational-principles.html`, `sdk.html`, `sdk-pages/*.html`, `styleguide.html`, `components.html`) with inline `<style>` blocks.

2. **Node.js/Strapi version**: Under `node-app/` — EJS templates in `views/`, CSS in `public/css/main.css`, route data in `server.js`.

## Rules

- When making any content, styling, or structural change, always apply it to **both** versions.
- Static HTML pages use inline `<style>` tags; the Node.js version uses `node-app/public/css/main.css` and EJS partials (`views/partials/`).
- Navigation data lives in `fallbackData.nav` inside `server.js` — always use this for nav (Strapi's flat NavItem can't represent nested dropdowns).
- Research page items use `fallbackResearch.items` in `server.js` (not Strapi research-cards, which are homepage cards).
- SDK documentation pages (`sdk.html`, `sdk-pages/*.html`) are static-only; they don't have a Node.js counterpart.
